---
block_id: 026
name: hub-bgp-neighbor-range
display_name: "Hub BGP Neighbor Range Configuration"
version: 1.0.0
category: core
device_role: hub
vendor: fortinet
platform: fortigate
min_fortios: "7.4.0"

description: |
  BGP neighbor-range configuration for SD-WAN hub. Accepts dynamic BGP
  sessions from spokes using neighbor-range instead of explicit neighbors.

  KEY: Hub accepts ANY spoke in the 172.16.0.0/16 range dynamically.

depends_on:
  - block_id: 025
    reason: "BGP base must be configured first"

provides:
  - hub-bgp-neighbor-range
  - hub-bgp-edge-group
  - hub-bgp-networks

parameters:
  - name: NEIGHBOR_GROUP_NAME
    description: "Neighbor group name for spokes"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "EDGE"

  - name: NEIGHBOR_RANGE_PREFIX
    description: "Spoke loopback range (prefix)"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "172.16.0.0"
    note: "Hub accepts BGP sessions from any IP in this range"

  - name: NEIGHBOR_RANGE_NETMASK
    description: "Spoke loopback range netmask"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "255.255.0.0"

  - name: REMOTE_AS
    description: "Remote AS for spokes (same as hub for iBGP)"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 65000
    note: "Hub and spokes use same AS for iBGP ADVPN"

  - name: ADVERTISED_NETWORKS
    description: "Networks to advertise to spokes"
    type: string
    required: true
    example: "10.250.250.0"
    note: "Hub LAN networks advertised to spokes"

  - name: ADVERTISED_NETMASK
    description: "Netmask for advertised networks"
    type: string
    required: true
    example: "255.255.255.0"

verification:
  commands:
    - "get router bgp"
  expected_patterns:
    - "neighbor-group: {{NEIGHBOR_GROUP_NAME}}"
    - "prefix: {{NEIGHBOR_RANGE_PREFIX}}"
    - "remote-as: {{REMOTE_AS}}"

rollback:
  commands:
    - "config router bgp"
    - "config neighbor-group"
    - "delete {{NEIGHBOR_GROUP_NAME}}"
    - "end"
    - "config neighbor-range"
    - "delete 1"
    - "end"
    - "config network"
    - "delete 1"
    - "end"
    - "end"

notes: |
  - Neighbor-range allows spokes to connect dynamically
  - No need to pre-configure each spoke as a neighbor
  - Spokes must use loopback IPs in the neighbor-range prefix
  - advertisement-interval 1 for fast convergence
  - soft-reconfiguration enables route refresh

---

config router bgp
    config neighbor-group
        edit "{{NEIGHBOR_GROUP_NAME}}"
            set activate enable
            set advertisement-interval 1
            set link-down-failover enable
            set next-hop-self enable
            set soft-reconfiguration enable
            set remote-as {{REMOTE_AS}}
        next
    end
    config neighbor-range
        edit 1
            set prefix {{NEIGHBOR_RANGE_PREFIX}} {{NEIGHBOR_RANGE_NETMASK}}
            set neighbor-group "{{NEIGHBOR_GROUP_NAME}}"
        next
    end
    config network
        edit 1
            set prefix {{ADVERTISED_NETWORKS}} {{ADVERTISED_NETMASK}}
        next
    end
end
